 space and time.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Ecology letters</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/a33a2c0ae02f2700b69a451e69c96494"><gtr:id>a33a2c0ae02f2700b69a451e69c96494</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Elmendorf SC</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2012-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1461-023X</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/466481EC-5BEA-49C8-91B6-227918E65D3B"><gtr:id>466481EC-5BEA-49C8-91B6-227918E65D3B</gtr:id><gtr:title>No evidence for compensatory thermal adaptation of soil microbial respiration in the study of Bradford et al. (2008).</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Ecology letters</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/a72d459eb7ee9f03754c0dc201045aa1"><gtr:id>a72d459eb7ee9f03754c0dc201045aa1</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Hartley IP</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2009-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1461-023X</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/6EF3A193-3F5A-4146-96AF-011E6B4313BC"><gtr:id>6EF3A193-3F5A-4146-96AF-011E6B4313BC</gtr:id><gtr:title>Ecological dynamics across the Arctic associated with recent climate change.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Science (New York, N.Y.)</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/876a481ff8d3a80da72f449cd9d33851"><gtr:id>876a481ff8d3a80da72f449cd9d33851</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Post E</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2009-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0036-8075</gtr:issn></gtr:publication></gtr:publications><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">NE/D005833/1</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>E4C03353-6311-43F9-9204-CFC2536D2017</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>20</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Atmospheric phys. &amp; chem